  "prompt": "How do I get Pikachu as my first Pok\u00e9mon in Pok\u00e9mon GO?",
  "response": "Getting Pikachu as your first Pok\u00e9mon in Pok\u00e9mon GO is a fun little Easter egg! Here's how you do it:\n\n1.  **Start a New Game:** If you've already started playing Pok\u00e9mon GO, you'll need to create a new account.\n\n2.  **Ignore the Starters:** When Professor Willow first presents you with the starter Pok\u00e9mon (Bulbasaur, Charmander, and Squirtle), **don't choose any of them**.  Just walk away.\n\n3.  **Walk Away Repeatedly:** As you move, the starter Pok\u00e9mon will keep respawning around you. Continue to ignore them and walk away. This might take several attempts. You need to walk a reasonable distance away each time, basically out of their immediate spawn range.\n\n4.  **After 3-4 Attempts:** Eventually, after walking away from the initial three Pok\u00e9mon several times, Pikachu will appear alongside them as a fourth option.\n\n5.  **Choose Pikachu:** Now you can tap on Pikachu to select it as your starter.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Patience Required:** This method requires patience. It may take several minutes of walking to get Pikachu to appear.\n*   **Doesn't Affect Gameplay Later:** Choosing Pikachu as your starter doesn't give you any significant advantage in the game. You can still catch the other starter Pok\u00e9mon later.\n*   **Works Every Time (As of the Current Game Version):** This method has been a consistent Easter egg since the game's launch and is expected to work, unless Niantic decides to remove it.\n\nEnjoy your Pikachu!\n",
